radiographic_examinations.findings: The visualized lung bases are clear. There is no pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, and bilateral adrenal glands are normal. The kidneys enhance symmetrically and excrete contrast promptly without hydronephrosis. The small and large bowel are normal in course and caliber without obstruction. The appendix is hyperemic, fluid filled, and dilated to 9 mm with mild adjacent stranding. There is a small amount of free fluid in the right lower quadrant. There is no drainable fluid collection. The aorta is of normal caliber throughout. There is no free air. No pathologically enlarged mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymph nodes are identified.
